  "text": "All [CITATION_1] hours or more, were included in the study. Exclusion criteria were the following: lack of arterial blood gas measurement, patients using ventilator devices without a tidal volume measurement, noninvasive ventilation, previous dependence upon MV, and oxygenation impairment by heart disease or pulmonary hypertension. Patients ventilated in another institution for more than 24 hours and transferred to our PICU were also excluded from the study. Two patients were on high frequency oscillatory ventilation, after a time of pressure ventilation. Only data from pressure ventilation were analyzed in these two, because of the inability to compare ventilatory variables.",
